        </dc:subject>
        <dc:title>Entropy regularizing activation: Boosting continuous control, large language models, and image classification with activation as entropy constraints</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>We propose ERA, a new paradigm that constrains the sampling entropy above given thresholds by applying specially designed activations to the outputs of models. Our approach demonstrates broad effectiveness across different domains: 1) for large language models(LLMs), boosting the AIME 2025 score for Qwen2.5-Math-7B by 37.4%; 2) for continuous control reinforcement learning agents, improving performance by more than 30% over strong baselines such as SAC on the challenging HumanoidBench; 3) for image classification, enhancing ImageNet top-1 accuracy by 0.69% for ResNet-50. These gains are achieved with a computational overhead of less than 7%. Our work validates output activation as a powerful tool for entropy control, opening a new direction for designing simpler and more robust algorithms.</dcterms:abstract>
        <dc:date>2025-10-10</dc:date>
        <z:shortTitle>Entropy Regularizing Activation</z:shortTitle>
        <z:libraryCatalog>arXiv.org</z:libraryCatalog>
        <dc:identifier>
            <dcterms:URI>
               <rdf:value>http://arxiv.org/abs/2510.08549</rdf:value>
            </dcterms:URI>
        </dc:identifier>
        <dcterms:dateSubmitted>2026-07-22 07:58:05</dcterms:dateSubmitted>
